name: Obverse Couture Fashion Collar in Vintage Cream or Smoke Grey
description:
Inspiration

My Saloukee 'To Cherish Collection' is inspired by historical and contemporary fashion. Whilst looking at the pleats, folds and repetition in couture garments, I became fascinated with forms that were interactive, non permanent and enabled movement. Taking the concept of expansion and contraction, my 'To Cherish' pieces reveal a snakelike motion, only conceivable through touch and wear.

---------------------------------------------------------


Description

Our couture collar (we feel) is one of my most exciting creation to date. It is the largest piece of jewellery designed and made so far and contains almost 250 individually closed rivets in its making. We would make any excuse to wear this with a smile because we love it, this would also be fabulous with the right wedding dress!

---------------------------------------------------------

Dimension/Size

Approximate dimensions: W 18cm x H 6.5cm.

---------------------------------------------------------

All jewellery is made by hand in England and comes beautifully packaged in our Saloukee branded packaging. We also include a care label with each piece to explain the unique nature of the product.

---------------------------------------------------------

Material Used

Hand folded, embossed, paper, rivets, satin ribbon.

name: Loops hand woven yarn necklace - Neons
description:
Description:

Loops is a durable and perfectly on-trend statement necklace designed with an emphasis on simplicity and fastened with a hand thread bound toggle.

Loops is also available in neutral, pastel pink, pastel blue and pastel grey. All jewellery is made by hand in England and comes beautifully packaged in our Saloukee packaging.

-----------------------------------------------------

Dimension/Size:

Approximate length - 25in (65cm), approximate knit width - 1in (3cm)

NB. Due to each piece being made by hand, the dimensions and colour of your necklace may vary slightly from the images provided, please be reassured that your purchase will be unique to you.

-----------------------------------------------------

Material Used:

Each piece is unique, individually hand knitted using thread bound yarn, and coloured by hand using a neon and pastel colour palette.

To keep such beautiful handmade jewellery looking its best, it will need a little bit of T.L.C. Please apply all perfume, skin and hair products and leave to dry before putting on your jewellery. Please also remove it before swimming, showering and bathing and store safely when it's not being worn.

name: Design & Make Paper Jewellery book
description:
Saloukee's creative director Sarah Kelly has just written and published her first book which offers a series of masterclasses by experts who work with paper, and features examples of work from a breathtaking array of over 100 international makers. 

Techniques covered include encasing, crocheting, moulding, sculpting, cutting and binding, with paper types ranging from origami papers, to found papers, to paper yarn. Whether you want to make a personal piece to preserve a paper treasure, or create high fashion jewellery for exhibition on the catwalk, this book offers inspiration, tips and techniques for everyone interested in working with this sensitive, ephemeral material.

The book features the work of new and established jewellers including world renowned Wendy Ramshaw, David Watkins and Nel Linssen. It also looks further afield to fashion designers Jum Nakao and Michael Cepress and paper artist Rob Ryan. This is your chance to buy the book and to venture into the world of all things paper for yourself.

Get yourselves a limited signed authors copy ONLY online here at saloukee.com.

name: Saloukee Paper & Polish service
description:
Here at Saloukee, we know that however much TLC you give your paper jewellery, it is simply not going to be invincible forever! 

We've come up with a service to replace the paper element of your jewellery (choose a new colour if you wish!) and polish up the silver, before sending it back to you for your wearing pleasure.

Saloukee is for life and not just for Christmas and anniversaries and treats and birthdays....why not re-love your pre-loved!

name: Saloukee Gift Voucher
description:
The perfect gift to give...

If you are wanting to purchase Saloukee jewellery as a gift and are finding it difficult deciding on colours, sizes or styles, what better solution than to buy a gift voucher and let your loved one make the decision themselves!

The Saloukee gift voucher can be used on any of the products available on our online shop. Once paid for, the voucher will be sent to the purchasers email address so that it can be printed out or forwarded on to that lucky someone in question. 

The voucher can be then be redeemed against any item put in your shopping cart by simply entering the unique voucher code at the check out.

Happy shopping!
